Defendant Casimier Lebronze Wright in court with attorney Eugene E. Detert.  Defendant Casimier Lebronze Wright in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 40 MONTHS, CONCURRENT with 13CF2152, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 350 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 16 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM 
TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 24 MONTHS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF SUPERVISION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking program;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs- bail to apply; 

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations  be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  The Court suggests the defendant seek vocational training through the Department of Corrections.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Appeal rights given.
